verbose_text: Analysis of chondrocyte death by terminal deoxynucleotidyltransferase mediated dUTP nick-end labelling (TUNEL) confirmed that abnormally increased apoptosis was occurring in the hypertrophic zone by 2 weeks of age, and increased further with age (~ 3-4-fold); however, the precise localisation of increased apoptosis within the different growth plate zones was not determined.
